rComments: One of the best professors I ever had. She's extremely helpful and I really enjoyed  being in her class. Attendence is necessary. Can get an A+ if you do your work on time. Only 3 term works: midterm, library assignment, and short paper. Then there's the final exam. All of them are fairly easy to do. Overall, quite interesting course.
Was a very nice woman, not too hard a marker..but her lectures had little to do with the material we were supposed to be covering.

an amazing professor who followed her lectures with fascinating stories, and was easily approachable during class and easy to contact through e-mail. highly recommend taking any class she is teaching.

I don't know what "So.not.smart.at.all" rater-retard was smoking all year because Speirs is brilliant.  She is an amazing orator and very passionate and knowledgeable.  I was in awe of her and felt very inspired by her lectures.  I got Apluses on all my essays too, so trust me over anyone who rates her negatively.  It was a joy to learn from her.
Super classy lady! Encouraging and approachable!
The most enthusiastic prof at U of T. So nice, and so helpful.

Although this class is very long (3 hours), she is very clear and concise.  She is seriously one of the nicest people I have ever met! is enthusiastic about the material and always offers you help for essays!...she is THE BEST JEF100 teacher and the books are waaaaaaaay better then other jef classes
SO. NOT. SMART. AT. ALL. She's a ridiculously nice lady, but the class contains NO discussion, and it's basically a three-hour, boring version of my high school English classes. Kill me now.
great prof, very knowledgeable, very helpful and sweet
clarity in her lectures, she is very engaging and motivating.
